# excalidraw-app Conventions

`excalidraw-app/` is the deployed application at excalidraw.com. It wraps `@excalidraw/excalidraw`
and adds app-layer concerns: collaboration, persistence, sharing, analytics.

## Architecture

```
excalidraw-app/
├── App.tsx              # Root component; renders <Excalidraw> with all app callbacks
├── app-jotai.ts         # Jotai store for app-level atoms (import from here, not "jotai")
├── collab/              # Real-time collaboration (WebSocket via socket.io)
│   ├── Collab.tsx       # Collab UI and socket management
│   └── Portal.ts        # Socket.io portal abstraction
├── data/
│   ├── firebase.ts      # Firestore read/write, encrypted with Web Crypto
│   ├── LocalData.ts     # localStorage / IndexedDB integration
│   └── fileStatusStore.ts
├── components/          # App-specific UI (not in the npm package)
└── share/               # URL-based sharing logic
```

## Key Rules

### Jotai
Always import atoms from `app-jotai`, never from `jotai` directly:
```ts
import { atom, useAtom } from "../app-jotai";
```

### Firebase
- Firebase is initialized lazily in `data/firebase.ts` — do not call Firebase APIs directly from components.
- All Firestore data is encrypted with AES-GCM before writing (see `data/encryption.ts`).
- Config is loaded from `import.meta.env.VITE_APP_FIREBASE_CONFIG` (JSON string).

### Collab / WebSocket
- The collaboration socket is managed exclusively through `collab/Portal.ts`.
- Never import `socket.io-client` directly from components — go through `Portal`.
- Collab state is scoped to `collab/` — do not put collab logic in `App.tsx` directly.

### App State vs Editor State
- **Editor state** (elements, appState, files) belongs to the `<Excalidraw>` component; read it via `excalidrawAPI` callbacks.
- **App state** (user auth, collab status, share links) is managed in Jotai atoms in `app-jotai.ts`.
- Do not store editor state in Jotai atoms — this creates synchronization bugs.

### Environment Variables
| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `VITE_APP_BACKEND_V2_GET_URL` | Sharing service GET |
| `VITE_APP_BACKEND_V2_POST_URL` | Sharing service POST |
| `VITE_APP_WS_SERVER_URL` | Collab WebSocket |
| `VITE_APP_FIREBASE_CONFIG` | Firebase JSON config |
| `VITE_APP_PLUS_APP` | Excalidraw+ URL |
| `VITE_APP_AI_BACKEND` | Mermaid/AI backend |

For local dev: copy `.env.development` values into `.env.local` and adjust.

### Build
```bash
yarn start               # Dev server (hot reload)
yarn build:app           # Production build → excalidraw-app/build/
yarn build:app:docker    # Docker-optimized build
```

### Tests
App-level tests live in `excalidraw-app/tests/`. Run with `yarn test:app --watch=false`.
